<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-04-30T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-04-30T17:00:00-05:00" n="538" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d538">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2055: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul at Harbin</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Jenkins</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-04-30T18:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">April 30,
                                        1921—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>For Johnson from Stevens.</p>
                        <p>“Your April 18, 4 [<hi rend="italic">5</hi>] p.m.<note n="95" xml:id="d538fn95">See telegram, Apr. 18, addressed to the Secretary
                                of State, <ref target="#pg_577">p. 577</ref>.</note> Technical Board
                            should issue positive instructions to railway management to make no
                            payments whatever except such as authorized by Board. Copy of these
                            instructions should be handed Chinese member of Board for transmission
                            to his Government.”</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>